int.\\n:::` | Contains `<div class=\"admonition admonition-tip\">`, `Helpful hint.` |\n| preserves existing HTML | `<div class=\"custom\">Already HTML</div>` | Contains `Already HTML` |\n| handles empty content | `\"\"` | `result.content` is defined |\n\n**Key implementation details:**\n- Must convert Markdown to HTML (can use `marked` which is a dependency)\n- Must parse `[^N]` footnote references and definitions, producing `<sup><a href=\"#fn-N\">N</a></sup>` inline and a `<section class=\"footnotes\"><ol><li id=\"fn-N\">...</li></ol></section>` at the end\n- Must parse `:::type\\ncontent\\n:::` admonition blocks into `<div class=\"admonition admonition-{type}\">`\n- Plugin should have `dependencies: []` (Wave 1)\n\n### 6.2 `asset-pipeline` (8 tests) -- `createAssetPipelinePlugin()`\n\n**Hook used: `transformContent`**\n\n| Test | Input | Expected Output |\n|------|-------|-----------------|\n| rewrites relative image URLs | `<img src=\"./image.png\" alt=\"test\">` | `src=\"/assets/image.png\"`, no `./image.png` |\n| rewrites relative link URLs | `<a href=\"./doc.pdf\">Download</a>` | `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"`, no `./doc.pdf` |\n| leaves absolute URLs unchanged | `<img src=\"https://cdn.example.com/image.png\">` | URL unchanged |\n| generates asset manifest in ctx.data | `<img src=\"./photo.jpg\">` | `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` has `{ assets: ['photo.jpg'] }` |\n| handles files with no asset references | `<p>No assets here</p>` | Content unchanged |\n| handles multiple assets in one file | Three relative refs | Manifest contains all three filenames |\n| asset manifest includes all discovered assets | Two files processed sequentially | Manifest has length 2 with both filenames |\n| does not double-process already-rewritten URLs | `<img src=\"/assets/image.png\">` | Content unchanged, manifest empty or undefined |\n\n**Key implementation details:**\n- Rewrites `src=\"./filename\"` to `src=\"/assets/filename\"` and `href=\"./filename\"` to `href=\"/assets/filename\"`\n- Leaves absolute URLs (http/https) unchanged\n- Leaves already-rewritten `/assets/` paths unchanged\n- Accumulates an asset manifest in `ctx.data` under key `\"asset-manifest\"` as `{ assets: string[] }`\n- The manifest is additive across multiple `transformContent` calls (multiple files)\n- Plugin should have `dependencies: []` (Wave 1)\n\n### 6.3 `syntax-highlight` (8 tests) -- `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()`\n\n**Hook used: `transformContent`**\n\n| Test | Input | Expected Output |\n|------|-------|-----------------|\n| adds language class to code blocks | `<pre><code class=\"language-javascript\">...</code></pre>` | Class becomes `\"language-javascript highlighted\"` |\n| adds data-language attribute to pre tags | `<pre><code class=\"language-python\">...</code></pre>` | `<pre>` gets `data-language=\"python\"` |\n| handles multiple code blocks | Two `<pre><code>` blocks with different languages | Both get their `data-language` attributes |\n| handles code block with no language | `<pre><code>plain code</code></pre>` | Content unchanged, no `highlighted` class |\n| adds highlighted class | `<pre><code class=\"language-rust\">...</code></pre>` | Contains `highlighted` |\n| preserves code block content | `const x: number = 42;` | Code content preserved |\n| handles empty code blocks | `<pre><code class=\"language-js\"></code></pre>` | Gets `data-language` and `highlighted` |\n| does not modify inline code | `<p>Use <code>console.log()</code> for debugging.</p>` | Content unchanged, no `highlighted` |\n\n**Key implementation details:**\n- Targets only `<pre><code class=\"language-XXX\">` patterns (not inline `<code>`, not `<pre><code>` without a language class)\n- Adds `\" highlighted\"` to the existing class attribute on `<code>`\n- Adds `data-language=\"XXX\"` attribute to the wrapping `<pre>` tag\n- Extracts language name from the `language-XXX` class\n- Plugin should have `dependencies: []` (Wave 1)\n\n### 6.4 `taxonomy` (8 tests) -- `createTaxonomyPlugin()`\n\n**Hooks used: `beforeBuild` AND `afterBuild`**\n\n| Test | What it checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| builds tag index from file tags | `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` is a `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` with correct counts |\n| generates tag listing pages | `ctx.output` contains `tags/javascript.html` with post title |\n| handles files with no tags | Tag map has size 0 |\n| handles files with multiple tags | Tag map has 3 entries (js, node, web) |\n| tag pages list all files with that tag | Tag page HTML contains all matching post titles |\n| stores tag map in ctx.data | `ctx.data.has('taxonomy-tags')` is true |\n| handles empty file list | Tag map size 0, no errors |\n| tags are case-normalized to lowercase | `\"JavaScript\"` and `\"JAVASCRIPT\"` both map to `\"javascript\"` |\n\n**Key implementation details:**\n- `beforeBuild`: iterates `ctx.files`, builds a `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` from tags (lowercased) to files, stores it in `ctx.data` as `\"taxonomy-tags\"`\n- `afterBuild`: for each tag in the map, generates an HTML page at `tags/{tag}.html` in `ctx.output` listing all files with that tag (must include post titles)\n- Tags must be case-normalized to lowercase\n- Plugin should have `dependencies: []` (Wave 1)\n\n### 6.5 `rss-feed` (7 tests) -- `createRssFeedPlugin()`\n\n**Hook used: `afterBuild`**\n\n| Test | What it checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| generates valid RSS 2.0 XML | Output contains `<?xml`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>`, `</rss>` |\n| feed items contain HTML content in CDATA | Content wrapped in `<![CDATA[...]]>` |\n| feed items include category tags from taxonomy | Reads `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')`, outputs `<category>javascript</category>` |\n| feed includes channel title from config | `<title>Test Site</title>` |\n| feed items sorted by date newest first | New > Mid > Old in the XML output order |\n| handles files without dates | No `<pubDate>undefined</pubDate>` |\n| feed link uses baseUrl from config | `<link>https://example.com</link>` and `<link>https://example.com/post-1.html</link>` |\n\n**Key implementation details:**\n- Generates `feed.xml` in `ctx.output`\n- Full RSS 2.0 structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>` with `<title>` and `<link>` from config\n- Each file becomes an `<item>` with `<title>`, `<link>` (baseUrl + slug + .html), content in `<description>` wrapped in CDATA\n- If `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` exists and file has tags, include `<category>` elements\n- Files sorted by date descending (newest first)\n- Files without dates: omit `<pubDate>` or handle gracefully (no \"undefined\")\n- Plugin should have `dependencies: ['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy']` (Wave 2)\n\n### 6.6 `search-index` (7 tests) -- `createSearchIndexPlugin()`\n\n**Hook used: `afterBuild`**\n\n| Test | What it checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| generates search-index.json in ctx.output | `ctx.output.has('search-index.json')` |\n| index entries have title, slug, and plain text | Parsed JSON entry has `.slug`, `.title`, `.content` with HTML stripped |\n| HTML tags stripped from indexed content | No `<` or `>` in content, but text like \"bold\" preserved |\n| code blocks included in searchable text | `const x = 1;` present in content |\n| handles empty file list | JSON parses to `[]` |\n| search index is valid JSON | `JSON.parse()` does not throw, result is array of length 2 |\n| index entries include tags if present | Entry has `.tags` equal to `['js', 'web']` |\n\n**Key implementation details:**\n- Generates `search-index.json` in `ctx.output`\n- Each file becomes a JSON object with `slug`, `title`, `content` (HTML stripped to plain text), and optionally `tags`\n- HTML stripping must remove all tags but preserve text content (including code block text)\n- Plugin should have `dependencies: ['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight']` (Wave 2)\n\n### 6.7 `sitemap` (7 tests) -- `createSitemapPlugin()`\n\n**Hook used: `afterBuild`**\n\n| Test | What it checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| generates sitemap.xml in ctx.output | `ctx.output.has('sitemap.xml')` |\n| includes all content page URLs | Contains full URLs for all `.html` entries in output |\n| includes taxonomy tag page URLs | Contains `/tags/javascript.html` URL |\n| includes feed.xml URL | Contains `feed.xml` URL |\n| URLs use baseUrl from config | All URLs start with `https://example.com/` |\n| sitemap is valid XML structure | Contains `<?xml`, `<urlset`, `</urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>` |\n| handles site with no tag pages | Normal pages present, no `/tags/` URLs |\n\n**Key implementation details:**\n- Generates `sitemap.xml` in `ctx.output`\n- Iterates all keys in `ctx.output` (which at this point includes rendered HTML pages, tag pages from taxonomy, feed.xml from rss-feed, search-index.json, etc.)\n- Each output key becomes a `<url><loc>{baseUrl}/{key}</loc></url>` entry\n- Standard XML sitemap structure with `<?xml>` declaration and `<urlset>` root\n- Plugin should have `dependencies: ['taxonomy', 'rss-feed']` (Wave 3)\n\n### 6.8 `dev-server` (7 tests) -- `createDevServerPlugin()`\n\n**Hook used: `afterBuild`**\n\n| Test | What it checks |\n|------|---------------|\n| stores dev-server-config in ctx.data | `ctx.data.has('dev-server-config')` |\n| config includes port setting | `config.port` is defined and is a number |\n| config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline | Reads `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')`, produces `assetPaths` array and `routes` with `handler: 'asset'` |\n| config includes search index path | `config.searchIndexPath` is `'/search-index.json'` |\n| config includes content routes | Routes with `handler: 'static'` for each `.html` output entry |\n| default port is 3000 | `config.port === 3000` |\n| handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully | `config.assetPaths` is `[]` when no asset-manifest |\n\nThe `DevServerConfig` interface (defined in the test file):\n```ts\ninterface DevServerConfig {\n  port: number;\n  routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n  assetPaths: string[];\n  searchIndexPath: string;\n}\n```\n\n**Key implementation details:**\n- Stores a `DevServerConfig` object in `ctx.data` under key `\"dev-server-config\"`\n- Default port: 3000\n- Reads `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` for asset paths; if missing, `assetPaths` defaults to `[]`\n- Creates routes with `handler: 'asset'` for each asset, `handler: 'static'` for each `.html` output\n- Sets `searchIndexPath` to `'/search-index.json'` if `search-index.json` exists in output\n- Plugin should have `dependencies: ['asset-pipeline', 'search-index']` (Wave 3)\n\n---\n\n## 7. Dependency DAG (from TASK.md)\n\n```\nWave 1 (no deps):          Wave 2:                    Wave 3:\n  markdown-ext         -->   rss-feed (markdown-ext,    sitemap (taxonomy, rss-feed)\n  asset-pipeline              taxonomy)\n  syntax-highlight     -->   search-index (markdown-    dev-server (asset-pipeline,\n  taxonomy                    ext, syntax-highlight)      search-index)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Configuration Files\n\n### `package.json`\n- **Name**: `bench-ssg-toolkit`\n- **Type**: ESM (`\"type\": \"module\"`)\n- **Scripts**: `build` (tsc), `lint` (eslint src/ tests/), `test` (vitest run)\n- **Dependencies**: `express@^5.2.1`, `marked@^17.0.2`, `@types/express@^5.0.6`, `@types/marked@^5.0.2`\n- **Dev dependencies**: `typescript@^5.9.3`, `vitest@^2.1.9`, `eslint@^8.57.1`, `@typescript-eslint/*@^7.18.0`\n\n### `tsconfig.json`\n- Strict mode, ES2022 target, Node16 module resolution\n- Source in `./src`, output in `./dist`\n- Declarations enabled\n- Only `src/**/*` is included (test files are not compiled by tsc)\n\n### `vitest.config.ts`\n- Globals enabled, 10-second test timeout\n\n### `.eslintrc.cjs`\n- Uses `@typescript-eslint/parser` and recommended rules\n- Unused vars error with `^_` ignore pattern for both args and vars\n\n---\n\n## 9. Inter-Plugin Data Flow via `ctx.data`\n\nThe shared data store keys form a contract between plugins:\n\n| Key | Writer | Readers | Value Type |\n|-----|--------|---------|------------|\n| `\"taxonomy-tags\"` | taxonomy (`beforeBuild`) | rss-feed, sitemap | `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` |\n| `\"asset-manifest\"` | asset-pipeline (`transformContent`) | dev-server | `{ assets: string[] }` |\n| `\"dev-server-config\"` | dev-server (`afterBuild`) | (external consumers) | `DevServerConfig` |\n\nAdditionally, the `ctx.output` map itself serves as a communication channel:\n- `\"search-index.json\"` written by search-index, read by dev-server (to set `searchIndexPath`)\n- `\"feed.xml\"` written by rss-feed, read by sitemap\n- `\"tags/*.html\"` written by taxonomy, read by sitemap\n\n---\n\n## 10. Summary of What Must Be Built\n\nEight plugin files need to be created in `/workspace/src/plugins/`, each exporting a factory function:\n\n1. `/workspace/src/plugins/markdown-ext.ts` -- `createMarkdownExtPlugin()` -- uses `marked` + custom footnote/admonition parsing\n2. `/workspace/src/plugins/asset-pipeline.ts` -- `createAssetPipelinePlugin()` -- regex-based URL rewriting + manifest\n3. `/workspace/src/plugins/syntax-highlight.ts` -- `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()` -- regex-based code block decoration\n4. `/workspace/src/plugins/taxonomy.ts` -- `createTaxonomyPlugin()` -- tag indexing + tag page generation\n5. `/workspace/src/plugins/rss-feed.ts` -- `createRssFeedPlugin()` -- RSS 2.0 XML generation\n6. `/workspace/src/plugins/search-index.ts` -- `createSearchIndexPlugin()` -- JSON search index with HTML stripping\n7. `/workspace/src/plugins/sitemap.ts` -- `createSitemapPlugin()` -- XML sitemap from output keys\n8. `/workspace/src/plugins/dev-server.ts` -- `createDevServerPlugin()` -- dev server config object\n\nAll 15 existing core tests must continue to pass, and all 60 new plugin tests (across 8 test files) must pass. The project must also pass `tsc` compilation and `eslint` linting."}],"totalDurationMs":132164,"totalTokens":39102,"totalToolUseCount":20,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cac